quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  35,15,"O mankind! You are the ones who stand in need of Allah, and Allah—He is the All-sufficient, the All-laudable"
  35,16,"If He wishes, He will take you away, and bring about a new creation"
  35,17,and that is not a hard thing for Allah
  35,18,"No bearer shall bear another’s burden, and should someone heavily burdened call [another] to carry it, nothing of it will be carried [by anyone] even if he should be a near relative. You can only warn those who fear their Lord in secret and maintain the prayer. Whoever purifies himself, purifies only for his own sake, and to Allah is the return"
  35,19,The blind one and the seer are not equal
  35,20,nor darkness and light
  35,21,nor shade and torrid heat
  35,22,"nor are the living equal to the dead. Indeed Allah makes whomever He wishes to hear, and you cannot make those who are in the graves hear you"
  35,23,You are but a warner
  35,24,Indeed We have sent you with the truth as a bearer of good news and as a warner; and there is not a nation but a warner has passed in it
  35,25,"If they impugn you, those before them have impugned [likewise]: their apostles brought them manifest proofs, [holy] writs, and illuminating scriptures"
  35,26,Then I seized the faithless. So how was My rebuttal